metadata.question: How parentgeenee works
metadata.answer: Step 1: Down the Parent Geenee app on your device and your child's device.   Step 2: Create a Safe Zone Let’s begin by setting up a Safe Zone to manage app access within a specific area:  1️⃣ Enter a valid address or use your current location. 2️⃣ Move the pin to the center of the building for accuracy. 3️⃣ Choose between Satellite View or Map View for better visibility. 4️⃣ Name your Safe Zone and set a radius to ensure the entire location is covered. 5️⃣ Select the apps you want to block within this zone.  ✅ Your Safe Zone is now created!  Step 3: Pair Your Child’s Device  1️⃣ Select their role as a child 2️⃣ Scan the QR code displayed on your phone to pair their device with your account. 3️⃣ Enable the required permissions on your child’s device.  That’s it! 🎉 Now, whenever your child enters the Safe Zone, the selected apps will automatically be blocked, ensuring a focused and distraction-free environment.  Let us know if you need any help—we’re here for you! 😊💜" nan nan

metadata.question: How do I add a Safe Zone/I am unable to create a Safe Zone.
metadata.answer: To add or create a Safe Zone in Parent Geenee, follow these general steps:Open the App: Launch the Parent Geenee app on your device.Navigate to Safe Zones: Look for the "Safe Zones" option in the app's settings or main menu.Set a Location: Use the map feature to select the area you want to designate as a Safe Zone. You may need to draw or mark the boundary on the map.Customize Settings: Adjust the settings for the Safe Zone, such as notifications when your child enters or exits the zone.Save the Zone: Confirm and save the Safe Zone.If you're unable to create a Safe Zone, try these troubleshooting steps:Update the App: Ensure you have the latest version of Parent Geenee installed.Check Permissions: Make sure the app has location access enabled in your device settings.Restart the App: Close and reopen the app to refresh its functionality.Contact Support: If the issue persists, reach out to Parent Geenee support at support@parentgeenee.com for assistance. nan nan

metadata.answer: We're Sorry to See You Go 😔We understand that every family's needs are different, and we truly appreciate the time you've spent with Parent Geenee.🔹 Uninstalling on a Parent’s Device – There are no restrictions. You can simply delete the app anytime.🔹 Uninstalling on a Child’s Device – To ensure your child's device remains protected, the app cannot be removed directly. The parent must first deactivate their account:1️⃣ Tap the menu (☰) icon in the top-left corner.2️⃣ Select ""Deactivate Account.""3️⃣ An OTP will be sent to your(parent) registered email – enter the OTP to confirm.4️⃣ Once verified, your account will be deactivated, and you can uninstall the app from your child’s device.These safeguards are in place to ensure your child’s digital safety while still allowing flexibility. They can request access to blocked apps through the Wish Request feature and even install new apps via the App Store with parental approval.If you’d like to learn more about these features or need help with anything else, just let us know—we’d love to assist you! 💜😊 nan nan

metadata.question: How can I acess app store/ play store
metadata.answer: TThe Parent Geenee app ensures that children cannot uninstall the app without parental authorization. However, if your child needs to access the Play Store (Android) or App Store (iOS), follow these steps:1️⃣ On your child’s device, tap the ☰ (Burger Menu) in the top-left corner.2️⃣ Select "Play Store Access" (Android) / "App Store Access" (iOS).3️⃣ An OTP will be sent to the registered parent’s email.4️⃣ Enter the OTP on the child’s device to verify their identity.5️⃣ Once verified, App Store access will be enabled for 15 minutes.✅ After 15 minutes, the Play Store/App Store will automatically be restricted again.Let us know if you need any further assistance! 😊 nan nan
